cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.DS

The paper deals with stochastic optimization of deep neural networks for AUC maximization, which is a problem commonly encountered in machine learning and computer vision. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition), and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper also discusses the use of Polyak-\L{}ojasiewicz (PL) condition, which is a theoretical concept in optimization and is relevant to sub-categories such as cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms).
